---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import { SITE_NAME } from '../../consts'
---

<Layout
  title="Sign-in guide"
  description={`How to sign in to ${SITE_NAME}: AT Protocol OAuth login with your Bluesky handle — no password needed.`}
  lang="en"
  path="connexion/"
>
  <h1>Sign in to {SITE_NAME}</h1>

  <h2>Your handle is all you need</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE_NAME} uses <strong>AT Protocol OAuth</strong>: just enter your <strong>handle</strong>
    (e.g. <code>yourname.bsky.social</code>) and tap <em>Sign in</em>. Your browser opens on the
    Bluesky sign-in page, you authorise access, and you're taken straight back into the app —
    without ever typing a password into {SITE_NAME}.
  </p>
  <p class="tip">
    📌 You can find your handle in your Bluesky profile → <strong>Settings → Handle</strong>.
    It looks like <code>yourname.bsky.social</code> or your custom domain.
  </p>

  <h2>No account yet?</h2>
  <p>
    Create a free account at <a href="https://bsky.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bsky.app</a>,
    then come back to {SITE_NAME} to sign in with your handle.
  </p>

  <h2>Alternative PDS providers</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE_NAME} works with any AT Protocol-compatible PDS — not just Bluesky. Just enter your
    handle: the app automatically resolves your PDS from your AT Protocol identity, no extra
    configuration needed.
  </p>

  <h2>Advanced: App Password</h2>
  <p>
    The sign-in screen also offers a <strong>handle + App Password</strong> login for cases where
    OAuth is unavailable (unsupported PDS, no browser access, etc.). This method remains available
    but is no longer necessary for most Bluesky users.
  </p>
  <details>
    <summary>How to create an App Password</summary>
    <ol>
      <li>Go to <a href="https://bsky.app/settings/app-passwords" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bsky.app/settings/app-passwords</a></li>
      <li>Click <strong>Add App Password</strong></li>
      <li>Give it a recognisable name (e.g. "SkateAT")</li>
      <li>Copy the generated password and paste it into the <strong>App password</strong> field on the sign-in screen</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="warning">
      ⚠️ The password is only shown once. Paste it directly into the app.
    </p>
  </details>
</Layout>

<style>
  h2 {
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  ol {
    padding-left: 1.4em;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin: 12px 0;
  }

  details {
    margin-top: 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
  }

  summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--brand);
  }

  .tip {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--brand);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin: 12px 0;
  }

  .warning {
    background: #fff8e1;
    border-left: 3px solid #f59e0b;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin: 12px 0;
    color: #7c5700;
  }

  code {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
</style>
